# Technical Decisions

## Why Next.js instead of React + React Router?
- Built-in routing and project structure
- Better SEO options (SSR/SSG) for public pages
- Single framework for public site + admin UI

## Why keep Express as a separate backend?
- Clear separation of concerns (frontend vs API)
- Better learning of REST, auth, middlewares, and deployment
- Easier to scale and version the API independently

## Database choice: PostgreSQL
- Strong relational model for achievements and statistics
- Reliable and common in production

## ORM choice: Prisma
- Great developer experience and type safety
- Easy migrations and schema evolution

## Auth choice: JWT (default: HttpOnly cookie)
- Simple stateless auth
- Safer browser storage when using HttpOnly cookies

## Infra: Docker + Compose + Nginx
- Reproducible environments
- One-command deploy
- Nginx handles TLS and reverse proxy
